I am currently recovering from a Eating disorder i’ve had since I was 13 and now i’m 20. And I vlog about it. Thankyou to both you & your Mum for not saying anything that is Larger body phobic and against junks foods. All bodys are beautiful and there is body diversity. Like your Mum said... you can be ANY weight as long as your happy inside. ANY body is beautiful and nobody is defined bu numbers!
And junk food is not bad. It’s all about Balance. Restriction is the biggest problem. All diets are dangerous unless medically advised by a doctor. The human body isn’t designed to be put into energy deficits. Let’s END diet culture. Whoever is reading this right now.... you are beautiful. Your weight is beautiful... as long as your healthy inside and your organs are functioning.. your breathing.. your vitamin levels are good... than you are healthy ❤️ a BMI means nothing. Only your body can tell you what weight it wants to settle at.
Love to everyone ❤️

Side note, I have been overweight since I hit puberty at 12, I have never had an issue with it because I have always felt "sexy" being curvy. Now at 53 I get people looking at me not believing how much I weigh because of how I carry myself and my own self-confidence. Being overweight does not mean unattractive x
